properties.areaDesc: Indian Wells Valley; Kern County Desert; Lake Isabella; Tehachapi Area
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 29 at 7:52AM PST until March 1 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 35 mph with frequent gusts around 55
mph. Occasional gusts over 60 mph are possible.

* WHERE...Lake Isabella, Tehachapi Area, Indian Wells Valley and
Kern County Desert.

* WHEN...From late tonight through Sunday afternoon. Strongest
winds will occur during late morning and early afternoon on
Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Power outages are possible. Travel could be hazardous,
especially for high profile vehicles such as campers and
tractor trailers.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roads expected to be impacted by strong
winds include Highway 178 through and below Walker Pass,
Highway 58 through and below Tehachapi Pass, Highway 14 and
U.S. 395.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH SUNDAY AFTERNOON
